                                  file manager

terminal file manager.

notes:

  - 'fm' only works in zsh.

  - all searches are case insensitive

installation:

  - add the 'fm' script to $PATH

  - to cd to last open directory in fm, add the following to your '~/.zshrc'
    file:

      #start fm, and cd to last directory on exit
      f() {   
              # store last directory in a temporary file
              tmp="$(mktemp)"
              fm ${1:=.} $tmp
              cd "$(cat "$tmp")"
              rm -f "$tmp"
      }

usage:

  j/'down'/^n - move one line down
  k/'up'/^p - move one line up
  g - move to the top
  G - move to the bottom
  l/'right'/^f - go to directory or open a file
  h/'left'/^b - go to the parent directory
  z - toggle hidden files
  ~/^h - cd to $HOME
  f - find line starting with a letter forward
  F - find line starting with a letter backward
  / - search pattern forward
  ? - search pattern backward
  n - next match
  N - previous match
  e/^k - use a fuzzy finder
  r - toggle preview
  s/'space' - select current file
  t - toggle displaying selected files
  d - set selection action to move
  y - set selection action to copy
  p - delete or copy selected files
  : - execute shell command
  q/'^c' - quit fm
